Java offers several ways to write to files:

**`Files.writeString(path, content)`** (Java 11+) — simplest, writes a string:
```java
Files.writeString(Path.of("out.txt"), "Hello");
```

**`Files.write(path, lines)`** — writes a list of strings (one per line).

**`BufferedWriter`** — for large or structured writes:
```java
try (var bw = Files.newBufferedWriter(path)) {
    bw.write("line");
    bw.newLine();
}
```

**`PrintWriter`** — `printf`/`println` style:
```java
try (var pw = new PrintWriter(path.toFile())) {
    pw.printf("Value: %d%n", 42);
}
```

Use `StandardOpenOption.APPEND` to append rather than overwrite:
```java
Files.writeString(path, text, StandardOpenOption.APPEND);
```

